153
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,867
But when I did as he said,

154
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,036
it really grew...

155
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,539
to three billion won in two weeks.

156
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:50,793
PETER: I was flying high ever since

157
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:53,212
and was put in charge
of NR Forum's private placement fund.

158
00:11:55,673 --> 00:11:59,301
You took orders from someone
you never met to manage all that money?

159
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:00,761
Do you think that's rational?

160
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,431
Prosecutor.

161
00:12:04,306 --> 00:12:07,351
Do you know how it feels to meet
your savior the moment before you die?

162
00:12:08,185 --> 00:12:11,605
He becomes your god and Buddha.

163
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:15,985
I had my soul sucked out of me,
and by the time I came to,

164
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:20,906
all of the money I was managing
had gone to Big Mouse.

165
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:23,534
PETER: This is so unfair.

166
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:26,120
Those jerks only used me.

167
00:12:26,203 --> 00:12:28,205
(ominous music)

168
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,417
You said you met him, right?

169
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:33,627
Yes, just once.

170
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,921
(rain pouring)

171
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:39,967
(ominous music)

172
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:48,642
PETER: I couldn't see his face
or hear his voice.

173
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:01,197
(music stops)

174
00:13:02,698 --> 00:13:03,783
Who's this?

175
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:06,952
The man who was in the car that night.

176
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:09,038
(suspenseful music)

177
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:22,009
PROSECUTOR: You saw Park Changho there
clearly with your own eyes.

178
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,351
You...

179
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:32,728
want me to give false testimony?

180
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,271
What false testimony?

181
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,607
He really is Big Mouse.

182
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:42,112
PROSECUTOR: We'll be happy
to finally close this annoying case.

183
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:45,574
The world will become a better place
after getting rid of an evil criminal.

184
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:47,993
I'll let you get off with probation.

185
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:50,663
You just have to nod in court
when I ask my questions.

186
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,041
(suspenseful music)

187
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,217
(tense music)

188
