happened to be Big Mouse.

203
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:08,741
CHANGHO: Wow.

204
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:12,870
What an amazing coincidence.

205
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,458
What's your point?

206
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,543
(tense music)

207
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,011
-(music stops)
-Are you Big Mouse?

208
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:31,430
(gasps, exhales)

209
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,556
(mutters)

210
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:34,934
JIHOON: You looked away.

211
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,020
What does that mean?

212
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:43,108
(laughs)

213
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:44,818
I was just joking.

214
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:47,154
Why are you taking me seriously?
You're making me feel bad.

215
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,450
Be clear what your objective is.

216
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,702
Is it getting the money back

217
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,038
or dragging me down?

218
00:15:56,538 --> 00:15:58,082
(exhales sharply)
Hey.

219
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:01,043
Obviously, it's the money.
Why would I drag you down?

220
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:02,127
(clicks tongue)

221
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,213
(ominous music)

222
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:06,715
Like you're so important.

223
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:09,927
-(scoffs)
-(thumping)

224
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,102
(clacking)

225
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,854
You'll chew your entire nail off.

226
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:22,314
(spits)

227
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:26,986
That guy Park Changho
really is Big Mouse, right?

228
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:29,947
How many times do I have to tell you?
Shall I brief you on the case?

229
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,949
What if Big Mouse retaliates?

230
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:34,743
I hear his organization is frightening.

231
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:39,206
We're the most frightening organization.
The Prosecution Service.

232
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:43,210
Relax and just follow my instructions.

233
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:45,295
(tense music)

234
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,427
MAYOR CHOI: He has never seen Big Mouse.

235
00:16:53,053 --> 00:16:54,388
What did you order him to do?

236
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:55,764
(shushes)

237
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:58,308
You're just the audience.

238
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,770
You just need to watch and enjoy.

239
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:03,605
♪ Ba bam ♪

240
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:09,528
(tense music)

241
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:22,666
(music stops)

242
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,793
PROSECUTOR: Have a seat.

243
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:31,133
(rhythmic thumping)

244
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,553
(tense music)

245
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,723
(exhales sharply)

246
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:40,350
I hear you're telling everyone in jail
that you're Big Mouse.

247
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,646
Otherwise, it's too much of a pain.

248
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,440
How'd you know the names of the druggies?

249
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:48,025
Someone gave them to me.

250
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:49,109
PROSECUTOR: Who?

251
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:53,489
Who knows?
I only received a sheet of paper.

252
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:57,659
PROSECUTOR: Okay.
Say whatever gibberish you want.

253
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:00,079
Hey.

254
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:01,830
You said you saw Big Mouse's face, right?

255
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:04,041
I did.

256
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:05,125
Look at him.

257
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:08,337
Look at his face, jerk.

258
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,798
(ominous music)

259
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:15,219
PROSECUTOR:
Look closely. See if it was him.

260
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:21,433
Do you know me?

261
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:23,894
I've never seen you before.

262
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:31,652
(music intensifies)

263
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:35,948
(alarm beeping)

264
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:41,453
JIHOON: Damn it. Why now of all times?

265
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:43,288
(exhales)

266
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:46,125
(inhales sharply)

267
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:48,544
(syringe piercing)

268
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:49,878
(mutters)

269
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:51,713
Insulin shots.

270
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,590
His diabetes must've gotten worse.

271
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:58,512
(gasps)

272
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:01,473
(gurgling)

273
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:02,558
PROSECUTOR: Hey.

274
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,309
What's wrong?

275
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:06,145
-What? What's wrong with him?
-PROSECUTOR: Come here!

276
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:08,147
-Hey.
-PROSECUTOR: Is anyone outside?

277
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:10,524
Hey. Why is he frothing at the mouth?

278
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:12,234
Hey, you. Hey.

279
00:19:12,901 --> 00:19:14,153
Hey!

280
00:19:14,778 --> 00:19:17,197
(gurgling)

281
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:21,410
Hey! Don't let him die, you bastard!

282
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,494
(thumps)

283
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,830
(Jihoon groans)

284
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,040
(Jihoon groans)

285
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:30,252
God...

286
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:31,920
damn it!

287
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,006
(ominous music)

288
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,640
JIHOON: How could this happen?

289
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:46,435
How could a witness go out
in a body bag...

290
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,480
from the Prosecutors' Office?

291
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:53,984
Park Changho's wife...

292
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:57,321
has Seo Jaeyoung's paper, right?

293
00:19:57,905 --> 00:20:00,490
It was a lie. I met her and confirmed it.

294
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:03,327
What if it wasn't a lie?

295
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,247
She's Big Mouse's wife,

296
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:12,669
the most dangerous woman in the world,
second only to Park Changho.

297
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:25,641
HEAD NURSE: Everyone not
on the night shift, check everything

298
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:28,227
including cleaning before two o'clock.

299
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:29,770
-NURSES: Okay.
-Also...

300
00:20:30,437 --> 00:20:33,690
why aren't you managing
the needles properly?

301
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:36,235
HEAD NURSE: One poke,
and you'll catch whatever they have.

302
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:37,653
I'll go home now.

303
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:40,280
-Ms. Ko?
-Yes?

304
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:43,450
You know our team
is volunteering this Sunday, right?

305
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:45,327
At Gucheon Penitentiary.

306
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:47,579
Yes, I heard.

307
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,748
You're working the night shift,
so you're excused.

308
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,377
It's okay. I'll go too.

309
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,629
You're so dense.
(chuckles)

310
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:58,298
You'd all prefer if she didn't go, right?

311
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,883
NURSES: Yes.

312
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:03,929
HEAD NURSE: Visit your husband
on your own time.

313
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:07,099
Volunteering at the penitentiary
is an official hospital event.

314
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:08,392
(chuckles)

315
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:11,144
(laughs)

316
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:13,146
I should go to the salon
and get my hair done.

317
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:16,275
Go do a lot of noble work.

318
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:20,821
HEAD NURSE: Why is she so proud?

319
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:24,825
Seriously. She's the most thick-skinned
in the entire hospital.

320
00:21:26,493 --> 00:21:28,495
(ominous music)

321
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:33,917
(indistinct TV chatter)

322
00:21:35,043 --> 00:21:37,587
SEO JAEYOUNG:
I heard you design jewelry for a living.

323
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:39,798
WOMAN: I make all kinds
of fashion accessories for women.

324
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:42,592
SEO JAEYOUNG: Can you make
a small necklace that will fit this?

325
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:46,722
A cross would be nice.

326
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:57,107
MIHO: Hi there.

327
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:00,485
It's the director.

328
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:03,447
MIHO: She looks good on camera.

329
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:06,325
This show is quite popular these days,
isn't it?

330
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:11,872
What's wrong with her?
Why was she so startled?

331
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,583
(ominous music)

332
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:18,462
(phone vibrating)

333
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:22,090
Hello?

334
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,925
JIHOON: Is this Ms. Ko Miho's phone?

335
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,010
Yes, it is.

336
00:22:25,093 --> 00:22:27,095
My name is Gong Jihoon.

337
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:29,890
You may not know who I am, but...

338
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:32,017
I do know you.

339
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:34,311
What is it?

340
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:41,276
(suspenseful music)

341
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:46,198
(exhales)

342
00:22:53,038 --> 00:22:54,414
(Jihoon mutters)

343
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:02,798
Welcome.

344
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:05,092
(Jihoon grunts)

345
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,762
I apologize for calling out of the blue.

346
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:12,599
You haven't eaten, have you?
I ordered you a steak.

347
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:16,478
That's a bit much. We just met
and don't plan on being friends.

348
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:19,231
Then you can watch me eat.

349
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:21,775
(laughs)

350
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:26,405
What I heard about you was true.
I heard you weren't very pleasant.

351
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:29,116
I'm a very busy person.

352
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:33,078
My calendar's full for half the year
with people I have to see.

353
00:23:33,161 --> 00:23:35,831
I squeezed you in
despite my hectic schedule

354
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:37,249
so please be understanding.

355
00:23:40,127 --> 00:23:41,336
Bring everything I ordered.

356
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:46,800
(ominous music)

357
00:23:52,722 --> 00:23:55,976
JIHOON:
I received an amusing piece of intel.

358
00:23:57,018 --> 00:24:00,814
That you have Seo Jaeyoung's paper.

359
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:03,567
Sell it to me.

360
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,446
How much will you give me?

361
00:24:08,530 --> 00:24:09,739
(mutters)

362
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,158
Whatever you ask for.

363
00:24:11,241 --> 00:24:12,284
(munching)

364
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:13,535
Forget it.

365
00:24:14,494 --> 00:24:16,621
It's very important to me as well.

366
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:17,664
(utensil clinks)

367
00:24:18,915 --> 00:24:21,585
Do you plan to use it
to get a degree somewhere?

368
00:24:21,668 --> 00:24:23,336
(laughs)

369
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:25,755
I need to save my husband

370
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:27,799
by finding the culprit
who killed Professor Seo.

371
00:24:29,384 --> 00:24:30,302
Hmm.

372
00:24:31,887 --> 00:24:32,971
(clears throat)

373
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:35,265
I ask out of curiosity.

374
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,685
Do you really not know

375
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:41,271
that Park Changho is Big Mouse?

376
00:24:41,354 --> 00:24:43,356
(ominous music)

377
00:25:00,957 --> 00:25:05,128
Park Changho said
the names of drug clients

378
00:25:05,795 --> 00:25:08,590
that only Big Mouse would know.

379
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:12,302
Don't you get it?

380
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:16,181
Your husband really is Big Mouse.

381
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:19,392
(laughs)

382
00:25:19,476 --> 00:25:22,187
MIHO: What do you mean?
Why would you become Big Mouse?

383
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:23,146
CHANGHO: Just for a while.

384
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:25,023
It's the only way
I can stay alive in here.

385
00:25:25,106 --> 00:25:26,483
What if you're found guilty?

386
00:25:26,983 --> 00:25:29,361
What if you get stuck here
living as Big Mouse forever?

387
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:31,530
It's to win the trial.

388
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:34,616
To clear my name and walk out of here
with my head held high.

389
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:35,909
I just need you to trust me.

390
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:38,662
We can go back to the way things were.

391
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:42,791
(scoffs)

392
00:25:42,874 --> 00:25:45,418
(laughs)

393
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:48,838
Is this why you called me here?

394
00:25:48,922 --> 00:25:52,592
Making time in your busy schedule
that's packed for half a year?

395
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:55,804
MIHO: Enjoy your steak.

396
00:25:58,807 --> 00:26:00,517
You read the paper, didn't you?

397
00:26:03,019 --> 00:26:05,397
JIHOON: Then you should know

398
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,440
that if you hold onto it,

399
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:11,319
you'll be in serious danger.

400
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:14,406
(tense music)

401
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,244
MIHO: Who will be in greater danger?

402
00:26:19,327 --> 00:26:21,204
My husband is Big Mouse, remember?

403
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:26,501
(tense music)

404
00:26:30,171 --> 00:26:32,424
(lips squeaking)

405
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,677
(fork clanking)

406
00:26:43,393 --> 00:26:45,812
(music stops)

407
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:51,401
(phone vibrating)

408
00:26:51,484 --> 00:26:53,695
KO MIHO

409
00:26:56,114 --> 00:26:57,198
(phone clicks)

410
00:26:58,116 --> 00:26:59,200
It's Ko Miho.

411
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:01,286
(pensive music)

412
00:27:01,369 --> 00:27:02,412
Yes, go ahead.

413
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:07,584
I just met Gong Jihoon.

414
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:11,004
He really believes Changho is Big Mouse.

415
00:27:12,172 --> 00:27:16,176
MIHO: It seems the list of names
you gave him saved him.

416
00:27:16,259 --> 00:27:17,469
Thank you.

417
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:20,847
Miho.

418
00:27:24,851 --> 00:27:27,145
Do you want to tell me something?

419
00:27:29,564 --> 00:27:30,732
No.

420
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:33,026
I'll be in touch.

421
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:37,656
(phone clicks)

422
00:27:37,739 --> 00:27:39,741
(tense music)

423
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:48,083
(music stops)

424
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:51,169
CHOI DOHA, HYUN JUHEE, SEO JAEYOUNG

425
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:54,547
This is Seo Jaeyoung's call history.

426
00:27:55,965 --> 00:27:59,135
They were all work-related,
so there's nothing useful.

427
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:02,555
When is his wife coming from the US?

428
00:28:02,639 --> 00:28:04,224
She has no plans to return.

429
00:28:04,891 --> 00:28:06,434
They were on terrible terms,

430
00:28:06,518 --> 00:28:09,396
so they were separated for over a year
before he died.

431
00:28:10,271 --> 00:28:11,940
You said he was into fishing.

432
00:28:12,023 --> 00:28:13,733
Was he in any club or anything?

433
00:28:13,817 --> 00:28:14,984
Nothing at all.

434
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:16,695
What, he went fishing alone?

435
00:28:16,778 --> 00:28:18,905
He was infamous for being a loner.

436
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:21,741
Hold on.

437
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:28,206
Look at this.

438
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:29,833
What are these?

439
00:28:29,916 --> 00:28:32,544
His profile pictures. Take a look.

440
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,588
MIHO'S FATHER: These aren't selfies.

441
00:28:35,672 --> 00:28:36,840
Someone else took them.

442
00:28:36,923 --> 00:28:38,883
Look at his smile. They were really close.

443
00:28:40,927 --> 00:28:42,929
(tense music)

444
00:28:45,765 --> 00:28:50,770
YOUNGSAN RESERVOIR
FISHING SPOT

445
00:28:51,396 --> 00:28:53,606
Do you really think
Seo Jaeyoung gave his paper

446
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:55,108
to the person who took this photo?

447
00:28:55,191 --> 00:28:57,235
That's what my gut tells me.

448
00:28:57,318 --> 00:28:59,320
(tense music continues)

449
00:29:00,655 --> 00:29:02,240
YOUNGSAN RESERVOIR

450
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:05,869
Excuse me. Have you seen this man before?

451
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:10,373
I have. He used to come fish
two to three times a month.

452
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:12,584
Did he come alone?

453
00:29:13,668 --> 00:29:14,753
Yes, at times.

454
00:29:15,336 --> 00:29:17,797
MAN: Why do you ask?

455
00:29:17,881 --> 00:29:20,049
We're looking for someone.

456
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:22,677
This man was murdered.

457
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:24,012
MAN: What?

458
00:29:24,095 --> 00:29:26,556
That's why we're searching for the person
who came with him.

459
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:29,768
Do you remember anything that may help?
Like their appearance?

460
00:29:29,851 --> 00:29:32,061
I only saw from a distance

461
00:29:32,395 --> 00:29:34,564
and he always wore sunglasses.

462
00:29:34,647 --> 00:29:37,567
Anyway, whenever they came together,
they never fished.

463
00:29:37,650 --> 00:29:39,360
They were busy being lovey-dovey.

464
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:42,989
-Lovey-dovey?
-He came with a woman?

465
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:45,283
Yes. I doubt she was his wife.

466
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:47,869
It was obviously an affair.

467
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:53,041
(tense music)

468
00:29:54,584 --> 00:29:57,170
(indistinct chattering)

469
00:29:57,253 --> 00:29:59,255
JERRY:
I'll start distributing the winnings.

470
00:29:59,339 --> 00:30:01,466
-INMATE 1: Yes.
-INMATE 2: Let's go.

471
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:04,135
Big Mouse.
Only people who bet on Big Mouse.

472
00:30:04,219 --> 00:30:06,012
JERRY: You'll pay for it
if you try to scam me.

473
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:08,973
Yongsan Butter. He bet three cards.

474
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:10,642
Three cards.

475
00:30:10,725 --> 00:30:13,311
-Room Four's leader. Two cards.
-ROOM LEADER: Two cards.

476
00:30:13,394 --> 00:30:14,395
INMATE: Yes!

477
00:30:14,479 --> 00:30:15,939
I'm No. 5914!

478
00:30:16,022 --> 00:30:16,940
Okay, 5914.

479
00:30:17,023 --> 00:30:18,691
-No. 5914.
-Mr. 5914 bet four cards.

480
00:30:18,775 --> 00:30:20,527
Okay, four cards.

481
00:30:20,610 --> 00:30:21,736
(cheering and laughing)

482
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,905
Yeongdeungpo Sparrow, two cards.

483
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:25,532
ROOM LEADER: Sparrow, two cards.

484
00:30:25,615 --> 00:30:26,866
INMATE: Hey!

485
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:28,284
Move!

486
00:30:30,036 --> 00:30:31,454
-Sir.
-Boss.

487
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:34,290
It's okay. Do what you were doing.

488
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:36,459
Don't mind me, okay? Go on.

489
00:30:36,543 --> 00:30:38,419
Hey. Go on.

490
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:40,296
-Okay, Miari.
-Miari, three cards.

491
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:42,006
Three cards.

492
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:44,425
-JERRY: Two cards for this guy.
-Two cards.

493
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:47,262
-ROOM LEADER: Two.
-JERRY: Weasel! Two cards for Weasel.

494
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:48,972
No. 2015 bet six cards.

495
00:30:49,055 --> 00:30:51,224
(inmates exclaim)

496
00:30:51,307 --> 00:30:52,684
INMATES: Big win!

497
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:55,019
Is that everyone? Anyone else?

498
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:58,773
Hold on. Moochangpo Mud Octopus?

499
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,442
-INMATE 1: Who's Mud Octopus?
-INMATE 2: Who is that?

500
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:02,986
-INMATE 3: Mud Octopus?
-INMATE 4: Come out, Mud Octopus!

501
00:31:03,069 --> 00:31:05,738
He bet 50 cards on Big Mouse,
but he hasn't shown up yet.

502
00:31:05,822 --> 00:31:07,156
Jerry.

503
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:09,993
Shouldn't the host keep what's left?

504
00:31:10,076 --> 00:31:12,912
-We can't really donate it now, can we?
-(chuckles)

505
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:15,248
Maybe the octopus crawled back
into the mud.

506
00:31:15,331 --> 00:31:17,959
After betting a whopping 50 cards. Gosh.

507
00:31:19,586 --> 00:31:21,588
(upbeat music)

508
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,802
Chairman Yang. You were Mud Octopus?

509
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:29,804
-CHUNSIK: What?
-ROOM LEADER: Goodness.

510
00:31:29,888 --> 00:31:31,890
The VIPs will be hurt...

511
00:31:31,973 --> 00:31:35,351
(sucks teeth)
...if they find out you bet on Big Mouse.

512
00:31:35,435 --> 00:31:38,605
You gamble based on your instinct,

513
00:31:39,105 --> 00:31:40,940
not on human relations.

514
00:31:41,024 --> 00:31:43,109
-(laughs)
-Pay up, punk.

515
00:31:43,192 --> 00:31:45,612
Here you go, sir. I wish you prosperity.

516
00:31:45,695 --> 00:31:46,988
That's 150 cards.

517
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:50,116
(applauding and cheering)

518
00:31:55,121 --> 00:31:57,123
(upbeat music)

519
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:02,670
(door closes)

520
00:32:12,555 --> 00:32:14,557
(music stops)

521
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,436
It's 100 bills per bundle,
60 bundles in all.

522
00:32:19,395 --> 00:32:21,189
Count it to make sure
it's 300 million won.

523
00:32:23,149 --> 00:32:24,233
I'm sure it is.

524
00:32:25,568 --> 00:32:27,737
We're done, okay?

525
00:32:29,530 --> 00:32:32,825
Thanks a bunch. I'll use it well.

526
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:40,500
(door opens)

527
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:44,796
I'll take my 10 percent commission.

528
00:32:52,470 --> 00:32:55,098
This is my cut. No complaints, right?

529
00:33:00,395 --> 00:33:02,438
(upbeat music)

530
00:33:04,941 --> 00:33:06,567
Let me buy some benefits with this.

531
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:10,196
I can be a VIP like them, right?

532
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:12,240
Money

533
00:33:12,782 --> 00:33:14,534
