We're asking you to save us!

788
00:52:54,129 --> 00:52:57,591
How about getting us transferred?
If we go to another detention center...

789
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:58,758
(Jihoon sighs)

790
00:52:59,301 --> 00:53:01,386
You know their organization
is spread nationwide.

791
00:53:01,469 --> 00:53:03,430
At least you get protected here.

792
00:53:03,513 --> 00:53:04,806
Do you wanna die in the gutter?

793
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:08,143
Then we'll get written medical diagnoses,

794
00:53:08,226 --> 00:53:09,936
so get us out on medical leave.

795
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:11,563
Yes. That's a good idea.

796
00:53:11,646 --> 00:53:15,483
That means we can get out
immediately, right?

797
00:53:15,567 --> 00:53:18,945
That's up to the judge's discretion,
so grease the judges for us.

798
00:53:19,029 --> 00:53:21,323
-Come on.
-DOOGEUN: Do it for us.

799
00:53:21,406 --> 00:53:24,534
-Listen. Changho terrifies me.
-DOOGEUN: Please.

800
00:53:24,618 --> 00:53:26,745
DR. HAN:
I swear he shoots bullets with his eyes.

801
00:53:26,828 --> 00:53:28,997
-Seriously. Let go.
-DOOGEUN: Come on, man.

802
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:31,041
-CHAEBONG: Please. Do this for us.
-Let go.

803
00:53:31,124 --> 00:53:32,375
-DOOGEUN: Hey. Please.
-JIHOON: Get off!

804
00:53:37,505 --> 00:53:42,510
CORRECTIONS LEADING IN HOPE
AND RIGHTEOUSNESS TOMORROW

805
00:53:45,388 --> 00:53:48,225
GUCHEON PENITENTIARY

806
00:53:48,308 --> 00:53:51,811
JIHOON: Was the ruler of this region
waiting for me?

807
00:53:53,396 --> 00:53:54,898
Did you see my wife?

808
00:53:55,899 --> 00:53:56,983
Gosh.

809
00:53:57,442 --> 00:54:00,946
She came running
and tattled on me already?

810
00:54:01,780 --> 00:54:03,073
What did you say to her?

811
00:54:03,156 --> 00:54:04,366
(inhales sharply)

812
00:54:04,449 --> 00:54:06,660
Well, obviously...

813
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:08,578
it wasn't anything pleasant...

814
00:54:09,412 --> 00:54:11,831
when everything she does
is annoying as hell.

815
00:54:13,708 --> 00:54:15,252
You may be the king in here,

816
00:54:16,378 --> 00:54:18,004
but the outside world is my turf.

817
00:54:19,923 --> 00:54:22,801
I heard you bothered my friends.

818
00:54:24,386 --> 00:54:26,429
Give it a rest, okay?

819
00:54:26,513 --> 00:54:28,181
For your wife's sake.

820
00:54:28,265 --> 00:54:30,642
(suspenseful music)

821
00:54:30,725 --> 00:54:32,560
It's cheating to mess with family.

822
00:54:33,937 --> 00:54:35,063
JIHOON: Cheating?

823
00:54:36,856 --> 00:54:38,650
The Manchu Invasion,
the Japanese Invasion,

824
00:54:38,733 --> 00:54:40,485
the Civil War, the Korean War...

825
00:54:41,695 --> 00:54:43,947
There is no such thing as cheating in war.

826
00:54:45,991 --> 00:54:47,325
(laughs)

827
00:54:47,409 --> 00:54:50,287
(phone vibrating)

828
00:54:51,121 --> 00:54:52,163
What is it?

829
00:54:52,247 --> 00:54:53,873
JIHOON'S WIFE: Did you send the flowers?

830
00:54:54,582 --> 00:54:55,792
What are you talking about?

831
00:54:55,875 --> 00:54:57,794
They came in your name.

832
00:54:57,877 --> 00:54:59,921
Why did you send crap like this?

833
00:55:00,505 --> 00:55:03,049
Are you that thoughtless?
I'm throwing them out.

834
00:55:03,133 --> 00:55:05,176
Do whatever you want. Throw them out.

835
00:55:07,095 --> 00:55:08,221
Hold on.

836
00:55:09,514 --> 00:55:10,849
What was the flower?

837
00:55:10,932 --> 00:55:13,893
JIHOON'S WIFE:
Chrysanthemums. White ones, at that.

838
00:55:14,436 --> 00:55:17,439
These were meant for a funeral
and you sent them to me by mistake, right?

839
00:55:17,522 --> 00:55:19,524
(suspenseful music)

840
00:55:22,277 --> 00:55:23,320
(phone beeps)

841
00:55:27,782 --> 00:55:29,117
Did you send them?

842
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:32,746
Did you send my wife...

843
00:55:32,829 --> 00:55:34,706
Thirty-four white chrysanthemums.

844
00:55:36,207 --> 00:55:37,500
She's 34 years old, right?

845
00:55:39,627 --> 00:55:41,004
(exhales)

846
00:55:48,678 --> 00:55:50,430
Should we do this without any rules?

847
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:52,599
That's really my forte.

848
00:55:56,603 --> 00:55:58,605
(music intensifies)

849
00:56:04,152 --> 00:56:06,154
(music stops)

850
00:56:07,197 --> 00:56:10,367
Mess with my Miho one more time,

851
00:56:11,451 --> 00:56:14,245
and I'll send you
the most heinous gift in the world.

852
00:56:15,997 --> 00:56:17,999
(tense music)

853
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:32,055
Where's Chairman Yang?

854
00:56:32,722 --> 00:56:34,516
Why do you want to see
Yang Chunsik suddenly?

855
00:56:34,599 --> 00:56:36,768
I'll give him whatever he wants.

856
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:39,896
Tell him to kill that bastard.

857
00:56:42,148 --> 00:56:45,318
What about the 100 billion won?
Don't you want your money back?

858
00:56:47,028 --> 00:56:48,655
(clears throat)

859
00:56:51,282 --> 00:56:53,159
(grumbles)

860
00:56:54,744 --> 00:56:55,745
(Jihoon mutters)

861
00:57:04,003 --> 00:57:05,588
(music fades)

862
00:57:05,672 --> 00:57:06,798
(door closes)

863
00:57:08,133 --> 00:57:10,301
CHUNSIK: Six.

864
00:57:11,511 --> 00:57:13,513
Seven. Eight.

865
00:57:14,389 --> 00:57:16,641
Nine. Ten.

866
00:57:19,602 --> 00:57:21,271
Boss, Big Mouse is here.

867
00:57:21,354 --> 00:57:22,564
CHUNSIK: What?

868
00:57:23,398 --> 00:57:26,067
(groans, grunts)

869
00:57:27,235 --> 00:57:30,488
Would you like to have
a deep conversation with me?

870
00:57:32,615 --> 00:57:33,867
Everyone out.

871
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:37,704
(ominous music)

872
00:57:38,663 --> 00:57:40,457
What did the VIPs give you?

873
00:57:41,040 --> 00:57:43,835
Why do you care to know?

874
00:57:44,419 --> 00:57:46,379
I wondered what great thing you got

875
00:57:46,463 --> 00:57:48,506
that you're loyal to those bad guys.

876
00:57:48,590 --> 00:57:49,924
(laughs)

877
00:57:50,008 --> 00:57:51,968
No one here is good.

878
00:57:52,051 --> 00:57:54,137
Everyone is a bad guy.

879
00:57:54,220 --> 00:57:55,722
(chuckles)

880
00:57:55,805 --> 00:57:57,557
You're being released soon, right?

881
00:57:58,224 --> 00:58:00,685
Did they promise you
a business opportunity?

882
00:58:00,768 --> 00:58:01,853
(inhales sharply)

883
00:58:02,437 --> 00:58:07,317
If you're going to tell me to betray them,

884
00:58:08,943 --> 00:58:09,986
just leave.

885
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:16,242
I'm here to talk business.

886
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:19,204
I'm considering investing in you,
Chairman Yang.

887
00:58:19,287 --> 00:58:20,455
Investing?

888
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:23,500
How can I trust you?

889
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:27,879
You're getting life at the bare minimum.

890
00:58:29,547 --> 00:58:31,049
Want to make a bet?

891
00:58:31,132 --> 00:58:34,677
On which of us gets out of here first.

892
00:58:34,761 --> 00:58:37,805
(laughing)

893
00:58:39,849 --> 00:58:41,851
(tense music)

894
00:58:49,067 --> 00:58:51,611
(Dr. Han whistling)

895
00:58:51,694 --> 00:58:53,905
(suspenseful music)

896
00:59:00,995 --> 00:59:02,080
What are you doing?

897
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,002
Where's Chairman Yang?

898
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:11,506
Geez.

899
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:13,841
(music stops)

900
00:59:14,425 --> 00:59:15,468
What is it?

901
00:59:15,552 --> 00:59:17,762
INMATE: Stay still. Don't move!

902
00:59:18,346 --> 00:59:19,347
Shut the hell up!

903
00:59:20,348 --> 00:59:21,391
Come on.

904
00:59:21,474 --> 00:59:22,850
(muttering)

905
00:59:22,934 --> 00:59:24,519
(Dr. Han grunts)

906
00:59:25,103 --> 00:59:26,771
INMATE: Does that hurt? Does it?

907
00:59:26,854 --> 00:59:29,357
Get up, you punk. Crazy bastard.

908
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:31,442
(music intensifies)

909
00:59:31,943 --> 00:59:33,987
INMATE: Punk, look at you.

910
00:59:34,070 --> 00:59:35,405
(muffled screaming)

911
00:59:35,488 --> 00:59:37,240
Let go, you bastards!

912
00:59:37,323 --> 00:59:39,492
INMATE: Get up.

913
00:59:39,576 --> 00:59:42,537
(screaming)

914
00:59:43,705 --> 00:59:47,083
(breathing heavily)

915
00:59:51,629 --> 00:59:53,631
(suspenseful music)

916
00:59:53,715 --> 00:59:55,883
(breathing heaviliy)

917
00:59:59,762 --> 01:00:01,264
CHANGHO: You know where this is, right?

918
01:00:03,016 --> 01:00:05,226
You guys welcomed me
very enthusiastically here.

919
01:00:07,186 --> 01:00:08,563
What should I do with you?

920
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:11,316
You guys hung me up here.

921
01:00:12,942 --> 01:00:14,944
(ominous music)

922
01:00:21,034 --> 01:00:22,327
Please let me go.

923
01:00:23,786 --> 01:00:25,163
Please let me go!

924
01:00:25,246 --> 01:00:26,247
(sobs)

925
01:00:33,087 --> 01:00:34,547
CHANGHO: That was what I said.

926
01:00:37,091 --> 01:00:38,301
(scoffs)

927
01:00:40,136 --> 01:00:43,181
I watched the dashcam video from your car.

928
01:00:44,057 --> 01:00:45,475
CHANGHO: All you did was drive.

929
01:00:45,558 --> 01:00:47,727
Jung Chaebong and Lee Doogeun
killed Seo Jaeyoung.

930
01:00:49,479 --> 01:00:51,606
Why are you sharing the crime?

931
01:00:52,273 --> 01:00:55,735
Murder and accessory to murder
are punished differently.

932
01:00:56,819 --> 01:00:57,862
You were an accessory.

933
01:00:58,821 --> 01:01:00,365
And Gong Jihoon instigated it.

934
01:01:07,914 --> 01:01:09,290
Confess...

935
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:11,834
at the trial.

936
01:01:13,336 --> 01:01:14,337
(hiccups)

937
01:01:16,339 --> 01:01:17,340
(hiccups)

938
01:01:17,423 --> 01:01:18,966
Those who killed him can't do it,

939
01:01:19,050 --> 01:01:21,010
but you can since you're not as bad.

940
01:01:22,929 --> 01:01:23,930
(hiccups)

941
01:01:24,013 --> 01:01:25,640
Why can't you answer?

942
01:01:31,688 --> 01:01:33,022
Do you refuse?

943
01:01:34,273 --> 01:01:36,025
(breathing nervously)

944
01:01:38,403 --> 01:01:39,612
Let's hang him.

945
01:01:39,696 --> 01:01:42,490
-INMATE 1: Let's hang him.
-INMATE 2: Let's hang him by the neck.

946
01:01:42,573 --> 01:01:44,075
DR. HAN (gasps): No.

947
01:01:44,158 --> 01:01:47,578
-INMATE 1: Get up, bastard.
-No! I have to go home.

948
01:01:47,662 --> 01:01:49,664
(suspenseful music)

949
01:01:50,832 --> 01:01:52,709
(grunting)

950
01:01:52,792 --> 01:01:53,918
No...

951
01:01:54,001 --> 01:01:55,920
(chair creaking)

952
01:02:00,049 --> 01:02:02,176
DR. HAN: I'll do it.

953
01:02:02,927 --> 01:02:04,137
I'll do it.

954
01:02:05,054 --> 01:02:07,598
I'll confess, so don't kill me.

955
01:02:08,433 --> 01:02:10,810
Please don't kill me.

956
01:02:11,978 --> 01:02:15,815
(groaning)

957
01:02:15,898 --> 01:02:18,317
(chair creaking)

958
01:02:18,401 --> 01:02:19,861
(clanking)

959
01:02:19,944 --> 01:02:21,946
(music intensifies)

960
01:02:23,322 --> 01:02:24,699
(Dr. Han groans)

961
01:02:29,370 --> 01:02:32,290
(choking)

962
01:02:33,583 --> 01:02:35,918
(gurgling)

963
01:02:38,838 --> 01:02:40,840
(ominous music)

964
01:02:48,264 --> 01:02:49,474
(gasps for air)

965
01:02:49,557 --> 01:02:51,225
(groans)

966
01:02:51,309 --> 01:02:53,686
(coughing)

967
01:02:53,770 --> 01:02:55,897
(gasping)

968
01:02:55,980 --> 01:02:57,982
(suspenseful music)

969
01:03:00,026 --> 01:03:01,194
You promised...

970
01:03:02,236 --> 01:03:03,446
to confess.

971
01:03:03,529 --> 01:03:05,782
(gurgling, breathing shakily)

972
01:03:13,748 --> 01:03:15,082
MIHO: You told me to trust you.

973
01:03:16,042 --> 01:03:17,502
You told me to leave it to you.

974
01:03:18,044 --> 01:03:21,339
But you've been running in place
for days like a hamster.

975
01:03:22,048 --> 01:03:23,591
What happened with you?

976
01:03:23,674 --> 01:03:26,260
You said finding mistresses
was your expertise.

977
01:03:27,303 --> 01:03:29,263
Did you pay me or something?

978
01:03:29,347 --> 01:03:31,224
Why do you keep complaining to me?

979
01:03:31,849 --> 01:03:35,144
Finding out that Seo Jaeyoung
had a mistress was huge in itself.

980
01:03:35,228 --> 01:03:37,980
Hey. Did you find that out? I did.

981
01:03:38,064 --> 01:03:40,650
Forget it.
Go into his social media account

982
01:03:40,733 --> 01:03:42,527
and find out everything on Seo Jaeyoung.

983
01:03:42,610 --> 01:03:45,988
You'll find a lead on that woman,
be it photos or something else.

984
01:03:46,072 --> 01:03:49,325
There's nothing to go into.
He didn't do any social media.

985
01:03:49,992 --> 01:03:51,786
Darn it.

986
01:03:53,663 --> 01:03:56,082
Hey. What about that innovation center

987
01:03:56,165 --> 01:03:58,751
that the head nurse disappeared inside of?

988
01:03:58,835 --> 01:04:01,212
Security's tight 24 hours a day,

989
01:04:01,295 --> 01:04:02,964
so it's hard to even get in.

990
01:04:03,047 --> 01:04:06,342
What if you were to get
the patients' blood...

991
01:04:07,552 --> 01:04:08,594
No, right?

992
01:04:08,678 --> 01:04:11,180
We may find something
if we analyzed the blood.

993
01:04:11,264 --> 01:04:15,476
There are cameras in every room, too.
Or I would've done it by now.

994
01:04:16,269 --> 01:04:17,270
MAYOR CHOI DOHA

995
01:04:17,353 --> 01:04:20,147
(phone vibrating)

996
01:04:24,235 --> 01:04:25,611
Hello, Mayor.

997
01:04:25,695 --> 01:04:28,656
MAYOR CHOI:
I'd like to meet. Where are you?

998
01:04:30,116 --> 01:04:32,118
(ominous music)

999
01:04:44,463 --> 01:04:45,631
MIHO: Mayor Choi.

1000
01:04:46,841 --> 01:04:48,718
Sorry I'm late.

1001
01:04:58,811 --> 01:05:00,271
When I was a child,

1002
01:05:01,063 --> 01:05:02,773
my father ran a dye factory.

1003
01:05:05,776 --> 01:05:09,864
A reporter wrote that the factory
dumped toxic waste without authorization.

1004
01:05:11,157 --> 01:05:13,367
My father even got arrested for that

1005
01:05:13,451 --> 01:05:16,871
and sued the paper and the reporter.

1006
01:05:16,954 --> 01:05:18,247
The result was...

1007
01:05:19,290 --> 01:05:20,458
miserable.

1008
01:05:21,584 --> 01:05:23,878
Father suffered from an illness
until he died,

1009
01:05:23,961 --> 01:05:28,215
and I decided to become a lawyer
to help people like him who were wronged.

1010
01:05:28,299 --> 01:05:30,301
(pensive music)

1011
01:05:31,093 --> 01:05:34,639
Sometime after I became a prosecutor,
I ran into our old factory manager

1012
01:05:35,973 --> 01:05:38,142
and heard the truth from him.

1013
01:05:39,310 --> 01:05:41,896
It was true that my father

1014
01:05:43,064 --> 01:05:44,315
secretly dumped toxic waste.

1015
01:05:45,274 --> 01:05:47,109
MAYOR CHOI:
Whenever it rained for three years.

1016
01:05:48,611 --> 01:05:51,906
Right then, I thought I was
the most unfortunate person in the world.

1017
01:05:52,448 --> 01:05:53,699
But now,

1018
01:05:55,159 --> 01:05:58,079
Miho, you are the most unfortunate person
in the world.

1019
01:05:58,162 --> 01:06:00,164
(ominous music)

1020
01:06:03,793 --> 01:06:05,378
Park Changho...

1021
01:06:07,713 --> 01:06:09,048
He's Big Mouse.

1022
01:06:09,674 --> 01:06:11,842
(suspenseful music)

1023
01:06:11,926 --> 01:06:15,304
MAYOR CHOI: You're being fooled
just as I was fooled by my father.

1024
01:06:17,056 --> 01:06:19,058
(tense music)

1025
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:23,521
(scoffs)

1026
01:06:25,314 --> 01:06:27,108
Not you too.

1027
01:06:27,817 --> 01:06:29,068
Changho is pretending...

1028
01:06:29,151 --> 01:06:31,362
I gave him a fake list of names.

1029
01:06:33,280 --> 01:06:35,783
MAYOR CHOI: Park Changho knew
the real names of the druggies

1030
01:06:35,866 --> 01:06:37,952
that only Big Mouse knew.

1031
01:06:38,661 --> 01:06:39,787
(gasps)

1032
01:06:39,870 --> 01:06:41,789
The witness who knew
what Big Mouse looked like

1033
01:06:41,872 --> 01:06:44,500
was poisoned to death
during the interrogation with Changho.

1034
01:06:44,583 --> 01:06:47,962
Everyone who had gone against him
in the penitentiary mysteriously...

1035
01:06:48,045 --> 01:06:49,171
MIHO: Stop it.

1036
01:06:51,007 --> 01:06:54,301
I don't care what you say.
I trust my husband.

1037
01:06:55,177 --> 01:06:56,971
He said he was Big Mouse.

1038
01:06:59,223 --> 01:07:00,933
He told me not to tell you.

1039
01:07:01,892 --> 01:07:03,894
(tense music)

1040
01:07:22,079 --> 01:07:23,539
I'm leaving.

1041
01:07:48,189 --> 01:07:49,231
(sighs)

1042
01:07:52,651 --> 01:07:54,653
(music intensifies)

1043
01:07:58,866 --> 01:07:59,909
(exhales)

1044
01:08:03,996 --> 01:08:05,998
(music stops)

1045
01:08:06,832 --> 01:08:09,210
(phone vibrating)

1046
01:08:10,336 --> 01:08:11,504
(sighs)

1047
01:08:11,587 --> 01:08:13,130
(sniffles)
Hey.

1048
01:08:13,214 --> 01:08:15,132
MIHO'S FATHER: The loan shark called.

1049
01:08:15,216 --> 01:08:18,552
Changho paid off his debt
of over 100 million won in cash.

1050
01:08:19,929 --> 01:08:21,597
Where do you think he got the money?

1051
01:08:22,181 --> 01:08:23,349
Have you heard anything?

1052
01:08:24,266 --> 01:08:25,643
(breathes heavily)

1053
01:08:27,103 --> 01:08:28,521
Let's talk when I get home, Dad.

1054
01:08:28,604 --> 01:08:30,731
(solemn music)

1055
01:08:30,815 --> 01:08:31,899
(phone beeps)

1056
01:08:32,942 --> 01:08:35,861
(sobs softly)

1057
01:08:43,577 --> 01:08:46,247
(sobbing)

1058
01:08:50,751 --> 01:08:52,419
(sobbing)

1059
01:08:52,503 --> 01:08:54,505
(solemn music)

1060
01:09:08,394 --> 01:09:10,104
(music fades)

1061
01:09:10,187 --> 01:09:14,483
(sobbing continues)

1062
01:09:18,779 --> 01:09:21,115
BIG MOUTH

1063
01:09:21,198 --> 01:09:23,200
